add a user : $sudo adduser <username>
      example: $sudo adduser lsa_user
      
Network settings: The ip address and the ethernet connections and other network connections can be viewed using the :
       comand: $sudo ip a   (or)  $sudo ip addr
       
Configuring services: 
   The services that run in the background are also known as daemons, services usually have a 'd' in last of their name, this denotes as a daemon. 
   The services are available in the /etc/ folder as mostly the services are available there
   For example: 
   $ sudo view /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf 
   
   Command to start a service:                  
   $sudo systemctl start <service_name>
   
   Command to check the status of a service:    
   $sudo systemctl status <service_name>
   
   Command to stop a service:                   
   $sudo systemctl stop <service_name>
   
   
   Command to auto-start a service: 
   $sudo systemctl restart <service_name>
